<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="German3" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">German,</orth> adj. akin: <cit><quote>those that are g. to him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.802" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 802</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>g. to the lion,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.344" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 344</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the phrase would be more g. to the matter,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.165" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 165</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>Cousin-german</emph>).
